{
  "texts": [
    "AI content evaluation approach and individual involvement in evaluationFirst, we assessed the correctness of responses based on the key answers of the MCQs.",
    "Then, subjective evaluation of the AI generated content was based on a modi ed version of the CLEAR tool [37].",
    "This involved assessing the content on three dimensions: (1) Completeness of the generated response; (2) Accuracy re ected by lack of false knowledge and the content being evidence-based; and(3) Appropriateness and relevance of content being easy to understand, well organized, and free from irrelevant content [37].",
    "Each dimension was evaluated using a 5-point Likert scale, with 1 indicating \"poor\" and 5 representing \"excellent\" [37].",
    "To enhance the objectivity of the assessment, a prede ned list of criteria was established through discussions between the rst and senior authors."
  ]
}